SIMPLE: harlot
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Harlot
<hw>Har"lot</hw> <pr>(-l⟦ocr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>harlot</ets>, <ets>herlot</ets>, a vagabond, OF. <ets>harlot</ets>,
<ets>herlot</ets>, <ets>arlot</ets>; cf. Pr. <ets>arlot</ets>, Sp.
<ets>arlote</ets>, It. <ets>arlotto</ets>; of uncertain origin.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A churl; a common man; a person, male or female, of low
birth.</def> <rj><au><mark>[Obs.]</mark></au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He was a gentle <qex>harlot</qex> and a kind.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person given to low conduct; a rogue; a cheat; a
rascal.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A woman who prostitutes her body for hire; a
prostitute; a common woman; a strumpet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harlot</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Harlot
<hw>Har"lot</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Wanton; lewd; low; base.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harlot</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Harlot
<hw>Har"lot</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To play the harlot; to practice
lewdness.</def> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harlotize</ent>⟦br⟧
